						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jaṭāvarmaṉ Sundarapāṇḍya I. Year 20: A.D. 1271.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">paṇams</hi> for a twilight lamp to be lighted in the temple of Amaraviṭaṅgap Perumāḷ at Pāriyūr by Ūraṉ Periya Piḷḷaiyāṇḍaiyār of <hi rend="italic">maṉaiya vēṭṭuvar</hi> community and a native of Pāriyūr in Kāñchikkūval-nāḍu. On accepting the money, the <hi rend="italic">śiva-brāhmaṇas</hi> who had the right of service <hi rend="italic">(kaṇi)</hi> in the temple agreed to maintain the lamp.</p>						

						</summary>
